Review: It still baffles me how the cinematography in Kore-eda’s films can be so simple yet so mesmerizing and elegant.
Looked good and - like all Spike Lee films - has a powerful message about gun & gang violence and patriarchy. Too bad it heavily uses ‘sexyness’, which quickly becomes dull and played out.
She was kinda a bitch, no?

Went in without knowing what it was about (title is a bit misleading), and although I can understand why people like this, I was bored throughout the entire film. Only the bridge scenes sparked my attention.
Kinda wished it explored the “nightmarish demonic hallucinations” more than settling for experimental drug after effects. Otherwise a good film with nice acting and a surprisingly good score.

Movie: We Need to Talk About Kevin
Review: Sweet baby Jesus, that kid is the devil incarnate.
Tot heden nog altijd het beste wat de Belgische/Vlaamse tv-industrie ons ooit heeft geboden. Samen met In de gloria, uiteraard.
Not sure what to rate this yet. Cinematography, camera work and production design were fantastic, but I feel a bit conflicted about the story development. Will have to let this one sink in first.
First half got me excited and amused, but got a bit bored and impatient from the second half on.
If I wasn’t so tired and distracted, this would probably have a higher rating. Will have to watch again.

Movie: Chicken Run: Dawn of the Nugget
Review: A fun movie for the whole family. Claymation is so unbelievably satisfying to look at, even though chickens with teeth will haunt my in my nightmares.

Plot is shallow as hell, despite having its moments. By far the most wholesome parents in cinema though, Patricia Clarkson and Stanley Tucci are amazing. Thomas Haden Church and Lisa Kudrow are great too.
